Encoding requirements are not listed explicitly in [Database Setup for Oracle|https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/DOC/Database+Setup+for+Oracle] documentation although it has been mentioned in [Configuring Database Character Encoding|https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/DOC/Configuring+Database+Character+Encoding] documentation:
{quote}
The recommended encoding is Unicode UTF-8 (the equivalent for Oracle databases is AL32UTF8).
{quote}

I see that UTF-8 encoding information are mentioned in other databases main pages e.g. MySQL, PostgreSQL. Some customers may stumbled upon/search for [Database Setup for Oracle|https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/DOC/Database+Setup+for+Oracle] documentation and missed out the encoding part so its best to include this information in the main page as well.

