We have a team who is responsible for creating and administrating a Space in Confluence for each project we work on. This team does not need to be able to view every space, however, just administer it.

We want to be able to give a group (or user) the ability to Administer a Space, including the ability to change permissions, without requiring that they can view the Space. 

Currently, to give access to the Space Admin section, a user must have Admin and View permissions, and also not be restricted from viewing the page.

