MySQL configuration for confluence didn't mentioned create a database with utf8 character set and collation which may caused some problem in Confluence. The correct queries was documented correctly at:
* https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/DOC/Configuring+Database+Character+Encoding

h3. Document to change: 
https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/CONF51/Database+Setup+For+MySQL#DatabaseSetupForMySQL-Step4.SetupyourMySQLdatabaseanduser

The same goes to other specific documentation for  v5.0,v.4.3 and etc.

h3. Changes to be made:

*From:*
{quote}
2. Create an empty Confluence database schema by running this command:
{code}
CREATE DATABASE confluence;
{code}
{quote}

*To:*

{quote}
2. Create an empty Confluence database schema by running this command:
{code}
CREATE DATABASE confluence CHARACTER SET utf8 COLLATE utf8_bin;
{code}
{quote}

